          "anchor": "discussion",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Set a speech channel’s reference constantvalue. The reference constant value is passed to application-definedcallback functions and might contain any value convenient for theapplication. The ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "speechInfo",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " parameteris a long integer containing the reference constant value. In contrastwith other selectors, this selector does not require that the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "speechInfo",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " parameter’s valuebe a pointer value. Typically, however, an application does usethis selector to pass a pointer or handle value to callback functions.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "This selector works with the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "SetSpeechInfo",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " function. ",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    }
